3940MDNode *
3941SwitchInstProfUpdateWrapper::getProfBranchWeightsMD(const SwitchInst &SI) {
3942 if (MDNode *ProfileData = SI.getMetadata(LLVMContext::MD_prof))
3943 if (auto *MDName = dyn_cast<MDString>(ProfileData->getOperand(0)))
3944 if (MDName->getString() == "branch_weights")
3945 return ProfileData;
3946 return nullptr;
3947}
3948
3949MDNode *SwitchInstProfUpdateWrapper::buildProfBranchWeightsMD() {
3950 assert(State == Changed && "called only if metadata has changed");
3951
3952 if (!Weights)
3953 return nullptr;
3954
3955 assert(SI.getNumSuccessors() == Weights->size() &&
3956 "num of prof branch_weights must accord with num of successors");
3957
3958 bool AllZeroes =
3959 all_of(Weights.getValue(), [](uint32_t W) { return W == 0; });
3960
3961 if (AllZeroes || Weights.getValue().size() < 2)
3962 return nullptr;
3963
3964 return MDBuilder(SI.getParent()->getContext()).createBranchWeights(*Weights);
3965}
3966
3967void SwitchInstProfUpdateWrapper::init() {
3968 MDNode *ProfileData = getProfBranchWeightsMD(SI);
3969 if (!ProfileData) {
3970 State = Initialized;
3971 return;
3972 }
3973
3974 if (ProfileData->getNumOperands() != SI.getNumSuccessors() + 1) {
3975 State = Invalid;
3976 if (SwitchInstProfUpdateWrapperStrict)
3977 assert(false &&
3978 "number of prof branch_weights metadata operands corresponds to"
3979 " number of succesors");
3980 return;
3981 }
3982
3983 SmallVector<uint32_t, 8> Weights;
3984 for (unsigned CI = 1, CE = SI.getNumSuccessors(); CI <= CE; ++CI) {
3985 ConstantInt *C = mdconst::extract<ConstantInt>(ProfileData->getOperand(CI));
3986 uint32_t CW = C->getValue().getZExtValue();
3987 Weights.push_back(CW);
3988 }
3989 State = Initialized;
3990 this->Weights = std::move(Weights);
3991}
3992
3993SwitchInst::CaseIt
3994SwitchInstProfUpdateWrapper::removeCase(SwitchInst::CaseIt I) {
3995 if (Weights) {
3996 assert(SI.getNumSuccessors() == Weights->size() &&
3997 "num of prof branch_weights must accord with num of successors");
3998 State = Changed;
3999 // Copy the last case to the place of the removed one and shrink.
4000 // This is tightly coupled with the way SwitchInst::removeCase() removes
4001 // the cases in SwitchInst::removeCase(CaseIt).
4002 Weights.getValue()[I->getCaseIndex() + 1] = Weights.getValue().back();
4003 Weights.getValue().pop_back();
4004 }
4005 return SI.removeCase(I);
4006}
4007
4008void SwitchInstProfUpdateWrapper::addCase(
4009 ConstantInt *OnVal, BasicBlock *Dest,
4010 SwitchInstProfUpdateWrapper::CaseWeightOpt W) {
4011 SI.addCase(OnVal, Dest);
4012
4013 if (State == Invalid)
4014 return;
4015
4016 if (!Weights && W && *W) {
4017 State = Changed;
4018 Weights = SmallVector<uint32_t, 8>(SI.getNumSuccessors(), 0);
4019 Weights.getValue()[SI.getNumSuccessors() - 1] = *W;
4020 } else if (Weights) {
4021 State = Changed;
4022 Weights.getValue().push_back(W ? *W : 0);
4023 }
4024 if (Weights)
4025 assert(SI.getNumSuccessors() == Weights->size() &&
4026 "num of prof branch_weights must accord with num of successors");
4027}
4028
4029SymbolTableList<Instruction>::iterator
4030SwitchInstProfUpdateWrapper::eraseFromParent() {
4031 // Instruction is erased. Mark as unchanged to not touch it in the destructor.
4032 if (State != Invalid) {
4033 State = Initialized;
4034 if (Weights)
4035 Weights->resize(0);
4036 }
4037 return SI.eraseFromParent();
4038}
4039
4040SwitchInstProfUpdateWrapper::CaseWeightOpt
4041SwitchInstProfUpdateWrapper::getSuccessorWeight(unsigned idx) {
4042 if (!Weights)
4043 return None;
4044 return Weights.getValue()[idx];
4045}
4046
4047void SwitchInstProfUpdateWrapper::setSuccessorWeight(
4048 unsigned idx, SwitchInstProfUpdateWrapper::CaseWeightOpt W) {
4049 if (!W || State == Invalid)
4050 return;
4051
4052 if (!Weights && *W)
4053 Weights = SmallVector<uint32_t, 8>(SI.getNumSuccessors(), 0);
4054
4055 if (Weights) {
4056 auto &OldW = Weights.getValue()[idx];
4057 if (*W != OldW) {
4058 State = Changed;
4059 OldW = *W;
4060 }
4061 }
4062}
4063
4064SwitchInstProfUpdateWrapper::CaseWeightOpt
4065SwitchInstProfUpdateWrapper::getSuccessorWeight(const SwitchInst &SI,
4066 unsigned idx) {
4067 if (MDNode *ProfileData = getProfBranchWeightsMD(SI))
4068 if (ProfileData->getNumOperands() == SI.getNumSuccessors() + 1)
4069 return mdconst::extract<ConstantInt>(ProfileData->getOperand(idx + 1))
4070 ->getValue()
4071 .getZExtValue();
4072
4073 return None;
4074}

4139/// removeDestination - This method removes the specified successor from the
4140/// indirectbr instruction.
4141void IndirectBrInst::removeDestination(unsigned idx) {
4142 assert(idx < getNumOperands()-1 && "Successor index out of range!");

4151 OL[NumOps-1].set(nullptr);
4152 setNumHungOffUseOperands(NumOps-1);
